

r.poly - 

r.poly extracts @glossary("area",16.glossary/area.def) edges from a @glossary("raster",16.glossary/rastdata.def) @glossary("map layer",16.glossary/maplayer.def) and converts
data to GRASS @glossary("vector",16.glossary/vector.def) format.  The program first traces the permieter
of each unique area in the raster map layer and creates vector data to
represent it.  The cell @glossary("category values",16.glossary/catval.def) for the raster map layer
will be used to create @glossary("attribute",16.glossary/attribu.def) information for the resultant vector
area edge data.

